OL,6,F"This is an exceptional case. The
OL,7,Finterests of justice would dictate
OL,8,Fthat a defendant should not be
OL,9,Fpenalised for fully examining legal
OL,10,Fissues.
OL,12,F"Mrs Sharkey made the fullest possible
OL,13,Fadmissions she was able to make in her
OL,14,Flengthy interviews. Her submissions
OL,15,Fhave never been a firm denial. They
OL,16,Fhave been an examination of the
OL,17,Fnecessary factors.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G7/8
